    question: "Is your window cleaning process safe for tinted or specialty glass?",
    answer: "Yes. Our process is completely safe for tinted, tempered, and specialty glass surfaces. We use distilled water, non-abrasive tools, and streak-free cleaning solutions that remove dirt and smudges without scratching or damaging delicate coatings.\n\nThis ensures your windows are cleaned thoroughly while preserving their clarity, finish, and longevity."
  },
  {
    question: "How often should I have my windows professionally cleaned?",
    answer: "Most homes benefit from professional window cleaning at least twice a year—typically in the spring and fall—to keep glass clear and maintain curb appeal.\n\nYou may want to schedule more frequent cleanings if your home is near:\n• High-traffic roads (dust and pollution)\n• Coastal areas (salt buildup)\n• Trees and landscaping (pollen, sap, and leaves)\n\nRegular window cleaning not only improves the look of your home but also extends the life of glass and frames by preventing buildup of dirt, hard water, and other contaminants."
  },
